Key technical points (implementation-ready):
- Function: Number.isInteger(value) -> boolean
- Exact behavior: returns true if typeof value === 'number' and value is finite and its mathematical value is an integer (no fractional part).
- Returns false for NaN, +Infinity, -Infinity, non-number types (strings, booleans, objects), and BigInt.
- Edge-case: floating point rounding can cause values that look non-integer to be represented as integer due to IEEE-754 precision; Number.isInteger(5.0000000000000001) may return true.

